benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid Request: Multiple success scenarios including default behavior and filtered retrieval (TC01–TC12, TC22, TC23, TC24).
Empty Response: Covered for no data and filters excluding all data (TC11, TC29).

Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of valid combinations and invalid inputs (accountId UUID validation, malformed dates, extra params, boolean flags defaults and false cases, combined filters) (TC02–TC10, TC12, TC13, TC25).
Server Error Handling: 500, 503, and 504 scenarios covered (TC16, TC19, TC30).
Security/Robustness: Injection/XSS inputs handled without leaking internals (TC17, TC26).
Performance/Load: Large dataset retrieval and response time expectation (TC18).
Resilience: Retry after transient network failure (TC27).
Regression/Backward Compatibility: Specific regression for withHistory and legacy defaults (TC21, TC22).
Content negotiation (success): Verifies application/octet-stream for default success (TC01).
gaps: Pagination: No scenarios for pagination behavior on large datasets (no page/size params, no next links, potential truncation).
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No tests for burst traffic returning 429 or headers like Retry-After.
Caching Behavior: No validation of ETag/Last-Modified, Cache-Control, or conditional requests (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since).
Content-Type consistency: Other successful filtered responses do not assert application/octet-stream, and error responses schema is asserted broadly but not per specific status codes.
Date edge cases: No tests for minDate only, maxDate only, minDate > maxDate (expect 400), timezone/ISO-8601 formats, or inclusive/exclusive boundary behavior.
Boolean parameter validation: No tests for invalid boolean values (e.g., withHistory=foo) or case variations (True/TRUE).
Accept header negotiation: No scenario for clients requesting unsupported media type (e.g., Accept=application/json) and expected handling (e.g., 406 or fallback).
Filtering nuances: No tests for case sensitivity/locale handling for queueName/serviceName, or unknown queue/service values returning empty set vs error.
Observability headers: No checks for correlation/request IDs in error responses as part of operational standards.
recommendations: Add pagination scenarios: default page size, explicit page/size params, navigation (next/prev), total count, and behavior with large datasets (verify no truncation without pagination).
Add rate limiting tests: simulate burst of requests to assert 429 Too Many Requests and presence/semantics of Retry-After and rate limit headers.
Add caching tests: verify Cache-Control and ETag on 200 responses; perform conditional GETs to assert 304 Not Modified behavior.
Assert content type for all successful variants: ensure application/octet-stream is returned for every 200 scenario; assert consistent JSON error schema and content type for 4xx/5xx.
Expand date validation: minDate-only, maxDate-only, minDate > maxDate (expect 400), timezone/offset handling, ISO-8601 formats, and boundary inclusivity (entries exactly at min/max).
Validate boolean params: withHistory/withInProcessing/withBusEvents/withNotifications with invalid values (expect 400) and case-insensitive true/false handling if supported.
Test Accept header negotiation: request unsupported media types to validate 406 or documented fallback; verify correct content when Accept=application/octet-stream.
Add filtering robustness: unknown queueName/serviceName return 200 with empty body; define and test case sensitivity expectations.
Consider adding observability checks: presence of correlation IDs and consistent error schema across 400/401/404/500/503/504.
